, where $C_l^{TE}$ crosses 0, are shifted to larger values by NFS. This\nshifting effect is as important as those causedby different inflation models\nand different baryon fractions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Nov 2008 04:12:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-04-15"}
